  "title": "FINANCE MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Client Relationship Management:</strong>Serve as the primary point of contact for construction clients, build strong, long-term relationships, and ensure client satisfaction.</li>\n  <li><strong>Sales and Business Development:</strong>Identify new business opportunities, acquire new customers (e.g., contractors, builders), and work to retain existing accounts and grow revenue.</li>\n  <li><strong>Market Awareness:</strong>Monitor industry trends, competitor activities, and changing customer needs within the construction sector to anticipate challenges and opportunities.</li>\n  <li><strong>Project Coordination:</strong>Work with internal teams (like operations, production, and technical staff) to ensure smooth project execution, resolve issues, and provide support for client needs.</li>\n  <li><strong>Strategic Planning:</strong>Develop and execute strategic account plans to meet client needs and company objectives, including contributing to tender submissions and technical aspects.</li>\n  <li><strong>Reporting and Forecasting:</strong>Prepare sales forecasts and performance reports, tracking progress against Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) and contributing to the planning of future revenue.</li>\n  <li><strong>Customer Support:</strong>Handle client inquiries, complaints, and ensure timely and effective resolution of issues.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Key Skills</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Strong sales and negotiation abilities.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Understanding of the construction industry and market dynamics.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency with project management and CRM software.</li>\n  <li>Ability to build and maintain long-term business relationships.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
